<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-09-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="350" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d350">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 6775/573.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President of
                                    Guatemala</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-09-16"><hi rend="italic">September 16,
                                    1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>It affords me the utmost pleasure to announce to you that the
                            International Central American Bureau, has been inaugurated under the
                            most favorable auspices.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">M. Estrada C.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>